WHAT IS HTML?
Html Stands for HYPER-TEXT-MARKUP language.
by using html we can develop or structure of  the wed pages.
html is introduced by the 'TIM BERNERS LEE" IN 1993 .
html standerd version is relesed in 1999.
html is case sensitive language.

Why Learn HTML?
Foundation of Web Development: HTML is the basic building block of all web pages. Knowing HTML is essential for any web developer.
Accessibility: Proper use of HTML ensures that websites are accessible to all users, including those with disabilities.
SEO (Search Engine Optimization): Well-structured HTML helps search engines understand the content of your web pages, improving search rankings.

Basic Structure of an HTML Document:
An HTML document typically follows a standard structur

<!DOCTYPE html>: Declares the document type and version of HTML.
<html>: The root element that contains all the other HTML elements.
<head>: Contains meta-information about the document, like its title and links to CSS stylesheets.
<body>: Contains the content that is displayed in the browser, including text, images, links, etc.
eg:
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <title>Page Title</title>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
  </head>
  <body>
    <h1>This is a Heading</h1>
    <p>This is a paragraph.</p>
  </body>
</html>
